set up the web server to support https  by setting up SSL/TLS certificates because the application redirct all non-HTTPS requests to HTTPS
updating your web server configuration (e.g., Apache or Nginx) to include SSL directives and certificate files
As part of enabling HTTPS and securing your web server setup,
ensure that the web server (e.g., NGINX) correctly forwards protocol headers to the application.
This setup ensures the application recognizes secure (HTTPS) requests "
proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme"

